<subSubSection id="D9C76503FFF0FFDFFF04EC1CFBC2FE8D" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="1485" pageId="5" pageNumber="1484" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="91623688FFF0FFDFFF04EC1CFBC2FE8D" blockId="5.[178,1085,1545,1596]" lastBlockId="6.[178,1085,218,299]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="1485" pageId="5" pageNumber="1484">
Comment: The original description is explicitly based on a single &quot;type&quot; from &quot; 
<collectingCountry id="E9CA7618FFF0FFDCFF0CEC33FEA1F99A" box="[186,329,1574,1596]" name="Iraq" pageId="5" pageNumber="1484">Mesopotamia</collectingCountry>
: Tanooma&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="F54C4B79FFF0FFDCFE78EC33FD9DF99A" author="CAMERON M" box="[462,629,1574,1596]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1484" pagination="249 - 251" refId="ref22979" refString="CAMERON M. (1940): New species of Oriental Staphylinidae (Col.). - The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine 76: 249 - 251." type="journal article" year="1940">CAMERON 1940</bibRefCitation>
). The species is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF0FFDCFC5FEC32FBD5F99A" baseAuthorityName="NORDMANN" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[1001,1085,1574,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anale">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF0FFDCFC5FEC32FBD5F99A" box="[1001,1085,1574,1596]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1484">S. anale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
especially by the finer and denser punctation of the abdomen. For illustrations of the 
<typeStatus id="4E66882AFFF3FFDFFF04EAEDFEE3FEA8" box="[178,267,248,270]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">holotype</typeStatus>
see 
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFF3FFDFFE8FEAEDFE79FEA8" box="[313,401,248,270]" captionStart="Figs 2-8" captionStartId="7.[178,218,1503,1523]" captionTargetBox="[182,1080,219,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-59@7.[178,1085,219,1487]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 2-8: Scymbalium persimile CAMERON, holotype (2-4) and S. nepalense nov.sp., paratype (5- 8): (2, 5) habitus; (3, 6) forebody; (4) abdomen; (7) aedeagus in lateral view; (8) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 2-6: 1.0 mm; 7-8: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301293/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">Figs 2-4</figureCitation>
. The male sexual characters of 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFD64EAEDFCA2FEA8" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1940" box="[722,842,248,270]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persimile">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFD64EAEDFCA2FEA8" box="[722,842,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. persimile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are still unknown. This species has been recorded only from 
<collectingCountry id="E9CA7618FFF3FFDFFD9CEB03FDBBFE8D" box="[554,595,278,299]" name="Iraq" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">Iraq</collectingCountry>
and South European 
<collectingCountry id="E9CA7618FFF3FFDFFC9AEB00FC87FE8D" box="[812,879,277,299]" name="Russia" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F54C4B79FFF3FFDFFCC8EB00FBF7FE8D" author="SMETANA A" box="[894,1055,277,299]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" pagination="579 - 624" refId="ref23296" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Subfamily Paederinae FLEMING, 1821. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 579 - 624." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
